        <p>Regular engine maintenance keeps your car running smoothly and prevents costly repairs. Follow these basic checks.</p>
        <h2>Tools Needed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Wrench set</li>
            <li>Engine oil</li>
            <li>Air filter</li>
            <li>Coolant</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Step-by-Step Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Check and change engine oil regularly.</li>
            <li>Inspect and replace air filter if dirty.</li>
            <li>Check coolant levels and refill if necessary.</li>
            <li>Inspect belts and hoses for wear.</li>
            <li>Ensure battery connections are clean and tight.</li>
        </ol>
